Showa Shell to Get 10 Billion Yen Loan to Invest in Solar Cells

-- B y   E m i   U r a b e   a n d   T a k u   K a t o
-- 
2011-06-28T00:53:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/showa-shell-to-get-10-billion-yen-loan-to-invest-in-solar-cells.html
Showa Shell Sekiyu K.K., a Japanese
oil refiner, will receive a 10 billion yen ($124 million)  bank
loan  to invest in solar-cell businesses.   Nine regional banks will provide the three-year loan,
arranged by the government-run Development  Bank of Japan (8301) ,
according to Akihiro Konishi, a senior vice president at the
state-backed lender.  The loan was reported earlier by Jiji Press.  To contact the reporter on this story:
占部絵美 in Tokyo at 
 eurabe@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
